<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>In the first round of the money creation process with a 20% reserve requirement, if a bank receives a $5000 deposit, what happens in the first three rounds?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">First: lend $4000, Second: lend $3200, Third: lend $2560</option>
            <option letter="b">First: lend $4500, Second: lend $4050, Third: lend $3645</option>
            <option letter="c">First: lend $4000, Second: lend $2000, Third: lend $1000</option>
            <option letter="d">First: lend $3500, Second: lend $2500, Third: lend $1500</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>With 20% reserve requirement: First bank keeps $1000, lends $4000. Second bank keeps $800 (20% of $4000), lends $3200. Third bank keeps $640 (20% of $3200), lends $2560. Each new loan is 80% of the previous deposit, following the reserve requirement pattern.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
